{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (signed, 0 blocking, 10 advisory). Triage + decisions (all advisory; resolved by committing design decisions here):\n- [E2 fbc10 path 'e.g.'] DECIDED: kernel package = src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/ (decide.py for Pass-3 core; __init__ re-exports).\n- [E2 ffdab / E1 f741d 're-export if needed'] DECIDED: YES re-export. passes.py re-exports pass3_decide/validity/impact/severity_label/GRADED_BINARY/DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD from the kernel; orchestrator.pass3_over_findings stays as a thin registry-resolver wrapper over kernel.pass3_over_findings. Tests + workflow_ops keep their current import sites (back-compat).\n- [F1 f5fa1 / E1 f0f39 / E5 fce85 test fixture + behavioral] DECIDED: offline equivalence is the existing deterministic gate-path tests (test_plan_review_workflow.test_decide_op_partitions_findings + test_plan_review pass3 behavioral cases by construction: validity 0/0.5, block/advisory/dropped/veto/indeterminate). They are ground-truth-by-construction AND pin the partition; both move/stay green pre- vs post-extraction. No new golden file needed (partition is pure-deterministic).\n- [T4 f635d rollback] JUSTIFIED N/A: pure in-process refactor, no runtime flag/deploy seam; rollback = git revert. Old code is replaced in the SAME commit the equivalence test guards, so a regression cannot merge.\n- [T7 f570e / T5e f39ce docs/ADR] DEFERRED to WS4 (the epic's dedicated kernel consumer-seam + doc deliverable). WS1 adds a kernel module docstring recording the pass3 contract + threshold parameterization.\n- [F4 f3534 beneficiary] JUSTIFIED: the named consumer is epic b744 (code review); WS1 is structural extraction (epic scope). No value-metric AC needed for an internal refactor."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782608301158282001,"uuid":"409a1084-dc81-4ef3-aa5a-d639f61ca6e1"}